This week we'll be discussing
the application of analytics

into very different
areas-- the Supreme Court

In the first lecture,
we'll discuss

how the decisions of the
United States Supreme Court

can be predicted before the
case even gets to the court.

In the second lecture,
we'll discuss the story

of D2Hawkeye, a medical
data-mining company I have been

involved with for
several years that
use analytics to gain an edge.

Through these examples,
we'll introduce the method
